OL,4,CTop scientists urge action against
OL,5,Cfaeces in rivers
OL,6,GHuman faeces in our rivers is putting
OL,7,Gthe public in danger and the risk will
OL,8,Gincrease without action, the UK's top
OL,9,Gengineers and scientists have warned
OL,10,Gin a report.
OL,12,FThe report led by the Royal Academy of
OL,13,FEngineering called for an upgrade of
OL,14,Fthe UK's sewage system and more
OL,15,Fwidespread testing of the country's
OL,16,Fwaterways.
OL,18,FProf Chris Whitty - England's chief
OL,19,Fmedical officer - said it was a
OL,20,F"public health priority as well as an
OL,21,Fenvironmental one".
